SIMPLE: encompass
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encompass
<hw>En*com"pass</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Encompassed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Encompassing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To circumscribe or
go round so as to surround closely; to encircle; to inclose; to environ;
<as>as, a ring <ex>encompasses</ex> the finger; an army
<ex>encompasses</ex> a city; a voyage <ex>encompassing</ex> the
world.</as></def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A question may be <qex>encompassed</qex> with difficulty.</q>
<rj><qau>C. J. Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The love of all thy sons <qex>encompass</qex> thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To encircle; inclose; surround; include; environ;
invest; hem in; shut up.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>encompassing</ent>⟦br⟧
